
🔥 COMPLETE FLOW (correct order)
✅ Step 1 → RDS Instance banao (Database)

👉 ye tumhara MariaDB replace karega

✅ Step 2 → S3 Bucket banao (File storage)

👉 ye tumhara files folder replace karega

✅ Step 3 → ERPNext ko in dono se connect karo
🟢 PEHLE RDS BANATE HAIN (step-by-step)
1. AWS → RDS → Create database

Select:

Engine: MariaDB
Template: Free tier (test ke liye)
2. Basic settings
DB instance name: erpnext-db
Username: admin
Password: strong password
3. Connectivity
VPC: same as EC2
Public access: ❌ No
Security Group: new create
4. Create DB

👉 5–10 min lagega

5. Important (bahut zaroori ⚠️)

RDS → Security Group → Inbound rules:

Type	Port	Source
MySQL	3306	EC2 Security Group

👉 agar ye nahi kiya → ERPNext connect nahi karega

6. Endpoint copy karo

Example:

erpnext-db.abc123.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com
🟢 AB S3 BANATE HAIN
1. AWS → S3 → Create bucket
Name: erpnext-files-akash
Region: same as EC2
Block public access: ❌ disable
2. IAM user create karo

IAM → Users → Create user

Permissions:

AmazonS3FullAccess

👉 copy:

Access key
Secret key
🟢 FINAL (IMPORTANT UNDERSTANDING)
Component	Kaha chalega
ERPNext App	EC2 (Docker)
Database	RDS
Files	S3
🔥 SHORT ANSWER (tumhara doubt clear)

👉 YES — pehle RDS aur S3 banega
👉 uske baad hi ERPNext ko connect karoge

